  "texts": [
    "IntroductionTime series forecasting (TSF) has been applied extensively in various real-world scenarios, including precipitation prediction [1], wind speed estimation [2,3], stock market forecasting [4], sales predictions [5], traffic flow estimation [6], weather forecasting [7], and electricity demand prediction [8], among others.",
    "The sequential nature, autocorrelation, and inherent patterns of time series data require specialized forecasting techniques [9].",
    "Consequently, over the past decades, researchers have focused on developing advanced models and methods capable of capturing the non-linear relationships present in time series data [10].",
    "Recently, data driven approaches have gained considerable traction in addressing data-driven problems, including TSF [11].",
    "Deep neural networks (DNNs) are becoming a superior alternative to the traditional statistical methods for time series forecasting, as they can model multiple time series concurrently."
  ],
